            . I paid the prisoner for a collar which my man bought of him - this is it.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182501130046"></xptr>ROBERT KENDREW. I live at Mr. Nicholls, the pawnbroker's - Blissett pawned this bridle at our house.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I did send that young man to pawn the bridle. The collar was throwing about the harness room, and I considered it useless. Mr. Hart's man had the collar some time, and I believe Mr. Hart gave me 2 s. 6 d. for it.</p>
               <p>One witness gave the prisoner a good character.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 42.</p>
